The Hawks have confirmed a warrant of arrest has been issued for Ace Magashule but the ANC Secretary-General says he knows nothing about it. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - ANC Secretary-General, Ace Magashule says he is not aware of any warrant of arrest. The Hawks confirmed the warrant is in connection with the R255-million asbestos audit contract in the Free State. READ: Warrant of arrest issued for Magashule Magashule maintains he is innocent and has done nothing wrong. "If it happens then it happens but I am not worried at all because I know I have not done anything wrong, as a law-abiding citizen of South Africa," said Magashule, who was campaigning in Soweto for Wednesday's by-elections. The former Free State premier is expected to appear in court on Friday.